ombined. And after pushing for civil unions right up
 until 2011, he now wants voters to believe that he=E2=80=99s a pioneer on =
the issue. What nerve!&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Let=E2=80=99s revisit O=E2=80=99Malley=
=E2=80=99s actual record rather than listen to his calculated amnesia.</spa=
n></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">&nbsp;In 2004, O=E2=80=99Malley told a =
Baltimore TV station, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not opposed to civil marriages.=
=E2=80=9D Also that year, he emailed a plaintiff in the state marriage laws=
uit
 that read, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m just supporting something I strongly belie=
ve in,=E2=80=9D referring to marriage equality. But by 2006, O=E2=80=99Mall=
ey=E2=80=99s position was shifting and he said, =E2=80=9CI was raised to be=
lieve that marriage is between a man and a woman. This is a fundamental iss=
ue of
 the state=E2=80=99s public policy, and a decision that ultimately should n=
ot be made by a single trial court judge.=E2=80=9D When confronted by gay a=
ctivists after issuing that statement, O=E2=80=99Malley disavowed any previ=
ous support of marriage equality.</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">After a 2007 Maryland court ruling limi=
ting marriage to opposite-sex couples, O=E2=80=99Malley issued the followin=
g statement as heartbroken gay residents were
 busy cancelling their weddings and mourning the court=E2=80=99s misguided =
decision: =E2=80=9CI look forward to reading the court=E2=80=99s full opini=
on, but as we move forward, those of us with the responsibility of passing =
and enforcing laws have an obligation to protect the rights
 of all individuals equally, without telling any faith how to define its sa=
craments. I respect the court=E2=80=99s decision.=E2=80=9D&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Privately, O=E2=80=99Malley had assured=
 gay rights activists and plaintiffs in the case that he supported marriage=
 equality, only to reverse course and ultimately
 invoke his Catholic religious beliefs to justify his support of discrimina=
tion.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">From 2008-2010, O=E2=80=99Malley public=
ly backed civil unions as bills to legalize marriage equality were defeated=
 in committee. He was even booed off the stage
 at a private LGBT donor gathering after advocating for civil unions over f=
ull marriage rights.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">In 2011, O=E2=80=99Malley finally said =
he would sign a marriage bill if passed. =E2=80=9CI have concluded that dis=
criminating against individuals based on their sexual
 orientation in the context of civil marital rights is unjust.=E2=80=9D Tha=
t bill ultimately failed.</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">It wasn=E2=80=99t until New York Gov. A=
ndrew Cuomo embraced the cause of marriage equality as a civil rights issue=
 =E2=80=94 and well after Maryland Attorney General
 Doug Gansler did the same =E2=80=94 that O=E2=80=99Malley evolved yet agai=
n. Whereas Cuomo made it clear even before he was elected that he supported=
 full marriage rights and then lobbied for the needed votes to pass it, O=
=E2=80=99Malley was =E2=80=94 until 2012 =E2=80=94the reluctant advocate,
 offering meek, private assurances of support but refusing to publicly embr=
ace the cause, even after winning a second term in a landslide.&nbsp;</span=
></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Though he eventually came around to ful=
l support and was instrumental in preserving the law after it went to refer=
endum, O=E2=80=99Malley was late to the marriage
 party and certainly doesn=E2=80=99t deserve credit for its success.&nbsp;<=
/span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">O=E2=80=99Malley has, for years, embodi=
ed the poll-driven milquetoast politician who checks the wind before stakin=
g out a position. Now he wants us to believe
 otherwise.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">=E2=80=9CWe have the ability as a party=
 to lead by our principles or are we going to conduct polls every time we t=
ry to determine where the middle is on any given
 day,=E2=80=9D he told NPR this week.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, s=
ans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">We should welcome O=E2=80=99Malley=E2=
=80=99s more progressive positions without forgetting his disappointing rec=
ord of saying one thing in private and the opposite when
 the cameras are rolling.</span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
